ce:section.ce:para:
To further evaluate the feasibility of BNS-CDs@Fe3+ sensor in practical application, this sensor was applied for detecting AA in human urine and serum. Before spiked with AA, the urine and human serum samples were diluted 100-fold. As shown in Table 1
                        , good recoveries and high analytical precision were obtained, further confirming the reliability and feasibility of the BNS-CDs@Fe3+ sensor for monitoring AA in biological samples. Compared with the reported methods (Table 2
                        ), the detection performance of BNS-CDs@Fe3+ for AA was excellent, no matter in colorimetric or fluorescent mode.
